name: PharmacyPhunQuiz
tweet: The mystery drug is C, pregabalin (Lyrica). The GABA analog is classed as an anticonvulsant and is indicated for focal onset seizures; However it is most often used for neuropathic pain. None of the other options match the description.  https://t.co/2ZsZCsHF2w

name: PharmacyPhunQuiz
tweet: It is an anticonvulsant although seldom used for that. Indications are for fibromyalgia and neuropathic pain. The many off label uses include RLS and menopausal symptoms. Drowsiness/dizziness are common. Which one?  A. Doxepin B. Phenytoin C. Pregabalin D. Milnacipran  See thread

name: PharmacyPhunQuiz
tweet: The mystery drug is C, pregabalin (Lyrica). The GABA analog is classed as an anticonvulsant and is indicated for focal onset seizures; However it is most often used for neuropathic pain. None of the other options match the description.  https://t.co/2ZsZCsHF2w

name: PharmacyPhunQuiz
tweet: It is an anticonvulsant although seldom used for that. Indications are for fibromyalgia and neuropathic pain. The many off label uses include RLS and menopausal symptoms. Drowsiness/dizziness are common. Which one?  A. Doxepin B. Phenytoin C. Pregabalin D. Milnacipran  See thread

name: PharmacyPhunQuiz
tweet: The mystery drug is C, pregabalin (Lyrica). The GABA analog is classed as an anticonvulsant and is indicated for focal onset seizures; However it is most often used for neuropathic pain. None of the other options match the description.  https://t.co/2ZsZCsHF2w

name: PharmacyPhunQuiz
tweet: It is an anticonvulsant although seldom used for that. Indications are for fibromyalgia and neuropathic pain. The many off label uses include RLS and menopausal symptoms. Drowsiness/dizziness are common. Which one?  A. Doxepin B. Phenytoin C. Pregabalin D. Milnacipran  See thread
